.fi/fi/yksikot/tse/yksikot/PEI/raportit-ja-tietopaketit/Documents/Liuhto_72005.pdf Its future competitiveness and role in the Baltic Sea economic region].\" [[University of Turku]].\n*Rogo\u017ca, Jadwiga, Agata Wierzbowska-Miazga, and Iwona Wi\u015bniewska. \"[https://web.archive.org/web/20141025174538/http://www.osw.waw.pl/sites/default/files/prace_41_en.pdf A captive island. Kaliningrad between Moscow and the EU].\" ''[[OSW Studies]]'', No. 41, July 2012.\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikivoyage}}\n\n*[http://www.konigsberg.ru/eng Kaliningrad travel guide]\n\n{{Kaliningrad Oblast}}\n{{Baltic fleet}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2012}}\n\n[[Category:Kaliningrad| ]]\n[[Category:East Prussia]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in the 1250s]]\n[[Category:Russian and Soviet Navy bases]]\n[[Category:Port cities and towns in Russia]]\n[[Category:Port cities and towns of the Baltic Sea]]\n[[Category:Populated coastal places in Russia]]\n[[Category:Members of the Hanseatic League]]\n[[Category:1255 establishments in Europe]]\n", "name_user": "Paulitzer", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTransportation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kaliningrad"}
{"title_page": "Khed, Ratnagiri", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2017}}\n{{more citations needed|date=August 2014}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name = Khed\n| other_name   = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = town\n| image_skyline           = Khed Naringi River.jpg\n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = Naringi River, which flows through Khed\n| pushpin_map             = India#India Maharashtra\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Maharashtra, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|17|43|04|N|73|23|38|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Maharashtra]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Ratnagiri district|Ratnagiri]]\n| established_title       = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date        = \n| founder                 = \n| named_for               = \n| government_type         = \n| governing_body          = \n| unit_pref               = Metric\n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_rank               = \n| area_total_km2          = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = 25\n| population_total        = 16892\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_rank         = \n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym      = Khedkar\n| population_footnotes    = \n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Marathi language|Marathi]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code             = 415709\n| registration_plate      = \n| blank1_name_sec1        = [[Human sex ratio|Sex ratio]]\n| blank1_info_sec1        = 0.96 [[male|\u2642]]/[[female|\u2640]]\n| blank2_name_sec1        = Literacy\n| blank2_info_sec1        = 80%\n| website                 = \n| footnotes               = Khed is situated in Mumbai\u2013Goa National Highway No. 66\n}}\n\n'''Khed''' is a town with a [[municipal council]] in the [[Ratnagiri district]] of the [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]. Situated on the [[Mumbai|Mumba]]i - Goa Highway, NH 66, it is surrounded by a number of villages.\n\nKhed is the headquarters of [[Khed taluka, Ratnagiri|Khed taluka]] which connects the district administration with the village administration.\n\n== Geography ==\nKhed is located at {{Coord|17.72|N|73.38|E|type:city}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/16/Khed.html |title=Maps, Weather, and Airports for Khed, India |accessdate= |quote= |publisher=Falling Rain Genomics, Inc.}} Retrieved on 23 October 2008.</ref> It has an average [[elevation]] of 25&nbsp;metres (82&nbsp;feet). [[Alphonso (mango)|Alphonso mangoes]] are grown in the area around the town. Khed lies between Kashedi Ghat and Bhoste Ghat. The region surrounding the town is mostly mountainous.\n\nThe [[Jagbudi River]] is a large river located in the area. Raghuveer ghat is mainly use for picnic spots.{{citation needed|date=October 2019}}\n\n== Culture ==\n\nKhed people like to live simple lifestyle. Gents in this region wear western outfits like pants and shirts. For home use, they use Barmuda pant due to humid and hot weather. Married women wear saree as regular outfit. Girls wear Punjabi dress on normal occasions. \nFor goddess function like Gauri Pooja women wears Nauari saree.\n\nGudhi Padwa is the famous marathi festival in this area which is the NEW YEAR as per MARATHI Calendar. Gudhi Padwa is celebrated on 1st day of the Marathi month Chaitra. On this festival every house owner decorates his courtyard with Rangoli. A very big Bamboo stick is decorated with Haldi-kumkum, Saree, Glass or Tambya and stood in every-bodies courtyard. People shares sweets on this occassion. Puran Poli is served in every home on this festival.\n \nEid is celebrated by the Muslim population.\n\n'RAJ YUVA Mahostav' & 'JC festival' (mela) is also organized in Khed once every year.\n\nHoli is one of the famous festival. Chakrmani (Mumbai and Pune staying people) returns to their homes on this festival. People collects dry trees and woods from forest and arrange in such a way that a big fire can generate. It assumes that after burning fire of Holi winter season is at its last stage.\n\nShimga is adjacent festival to Holi. Once the Holi is over villagers decorates Palkhi (Gods small home to carry over the villagers home). Small staues of the god are put in the Palkhi and Palhi is moved across the village for gods service. in many areas Shimga is celebrated for 7 days. Palkhi stays at Mankaries house in night. In some areas Kirtan and Bhajans are played in nights to serve God. Some people arranges Satynarayan Pooja and gives food as Prasad to devotees. \n \nGanpati Festival is most famous in this region. Every outstation person returns to his/her home on this festival. Mangala gaur is famous for Ladies cultural activities. People play Dholki, Tashya and Ganpati Musics/Songs, Bhajans on these days. In many areas people arrange different amusement activities for devotees to celebrate whole night. On the arrival of Gauri (3rd of 4th day of Ganpati festival based on Tithee) people cook special food in their houses like Mutton-wade, Chicken-wade etc. \n\nThree yearly Yatra is celebrated in Some villages. It is festival goddess Kalkai, Manai, Jholai etc. A huge long Teak wood stick is hanged horizontally on the standing pole in front of the temple in balance condition and is rotated by pilgrims. Many stalls are arranged by small businessman like cold drinks, wadapav, Laddu, Ice creams, play games etc.\nIn some areas Tamasha is played to entertain gathered people.\n\nDasara and Diwali is also a famous festival and Chakli, Shankarpli and Pohe are served in every home on Diwali festival.\n\nDassara is celebrated for 9 days. on 1st day Ghat-sthapana is done and on 9th days it is dissolved. \n\nBaras is also a small festival on this day Palkhi is decorated for the devotees.\n\n<ref>Haldi Kumkum</ref> Haldai Kumkum is a festival of married women. On this day many women visits to other woman and wish and greet her for long life of her husband. Exchange of small gifts is done on this occasion. Most women wear Green colored Sarees and Green Bangles on this day. \n\n[[Ram Navmi]] festival is celebrated in Laxmi Narayan Temple. It is celebrated for 10 days starting from Gudi Padva. \n \nOne of the most important attractions of Khed is the annual rally conducted on the occasion of SHIVJAYANTI.\n\nAlso KHED is known for huge rally conduction on the occasion of  and EID MILADUNNABI ([[Mawlid]]) in all over [[Ratnagiri]] district.{{citation needed|date=October 2019}}\n\n== Food ==\n[[Vada pav|Vada-Pav]] is a popular snack in this city.{{citation needed|date=October 2019}} Vade-Mutton is a popular dish in the khed. The staple diet is rice and fish. Ghavane is one of the main dishes in the menu which prepared by the rice flour, eaten as Breakfast. Also, '''Monga''' is a famous food item called as \"[https://maharashtratimes.indiatimes.com/food-recipes/chicken-popti-raigad/articleshow/56147411.cms Popati]\" in north konkan.\n\nMost Farmer eat Jhunaka Bhakri or Sukat Bhakri as breakfast on Farms. Chatni Bhakri is the most tasty item served in homes. Garam Masala is used for cooking vegetables.\n\n== Places to visit ==\nThe Bhagwan Parshuram Temple is located in the city on NH-66. the Temple is on the hilly area of [[Khed City]] and also the mid location from Khed as well as Chiplun. Raghuvir ghat is one of the best picnic spot in khed specially in rainy & winter season.\nKalkai temple is one of the best places to visit.\nThe Jalal Shah Baba Dargah is located in the city on NH.66. the Dargah is on the Veral Gav next to Khed Railway station\n\nRasalgad is the Fort located in the Khed Taluka. The way to Rasalgad passes from Khed City by crossing the [[Bharana Naka]] Junction and many other villages such as [[Sukivali]], [[Kudoshi]], Tale-Mandave, Bharade, Kulwandi, Tisangi, Ambawali, Shirgaon, Khopi, Bijghar, Hedali, kandoshi(Aai ramvardayani temple), mahipatgad fort, also in summer best place for swimmers vakvali water park near from khed.\n\n== Demographics ==\nThe 2001 Indian [[census]] reported that Khed had a [[population]] of 13,813.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Census 2001 Population Finder: Maharashtra: Ratnagiri: Khed: Khed (M.Cl.)|publisher=Office of The Registrar General & Census Commissioner, Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India|url=http://censusindia.gov.in/PopulationFinder/View_Village_Population.aspx?pcaid=3119&category=M.Cl.}}</ref> Males constituted 49% of the population and females 51%. Khed had an average literacy rate of 97%, which was higher than the national average of 69.5%. The literacy rate among males was 98%, and among females, it was 96%.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040616075334/http://www.censusindia.net/results/town.php?stad=A&state5=999|archivedate=2004-06-16|title= Census of India 2001: Data from the 2001 Census, including cities, villages, and towns  (Provisional)|accessdate=2008-11-01|publisher= Census Commission of India}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2011 Indian census, the town of Khed [listed] 15,249 inhabitants.<ref name=\"NPR-2011-Khed\">{{Cite web|title=NPR Report: Maharashtra: Ratnagiri: Khed|year=2011|publisher=National Population Register, Ministry of Home Affairs, Government of India|url=http://censusindia.gov.in/NprStateReport.aspx?stcd=27&distcd=32&tslcode=003}}</ref>\n\n== Industry ==\nSeveral factories [that produce] [[Chemical industry|chemicals]] and [[pharmaceuticals]] are located in Khed.  Furthermore, the [[Maharashtra Industrial Development Corporation]] (MIDC) has developed the Lote-Parshuram industrial area in Khed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.midcindia.org/MIDCWebSite/investment/industrial/IndustrialDetails.aspx?id=60 |title=Lote-Parshuram (Group D+) Industrial Area Details |publisher=Maharashtra Industrial Development Corporation |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080828175818/http://www.midcindia.org/MIDCWebSite/investment/industrial/IndustrialDetails.aspx?id=60 |archivedate=28 August 2008 }}</ref>\n\n== Transport ==\n[[File:Khed Railway Station.jpg|thumb|right|Khed Railway Station]]\nKhed lies off National Highway [[National Highway 66 (India)|NH-66]], popularly known as Mumbai-Goa Highway, which connects Khed with cities like [[Mangalore]], [[Panaji]], [[Madgaon]], [[Karwar]] and [[Udupi]]. The Bharna Naka \u2013 Khed road, part of state highway SH-106, connects NH-66 to the town of Khed. Khed has a railway station on the [[Konkan Railway]] line and a [[Maharashtra State Road Transport Corporation]] (MSRTC) bus station connecting Khed taluka to major cities in Maharashtra.\n\nKhed railway station connects three talukas (Dapoli, Mandangad, and Khed) to the railway map of India.\n\n==Education==\nMany schools and colleges in Khed are in English, [[Urdu]] and Marathi Medium.\n\n* GHARDA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY, LAVEL (MUMBAI-GOA HIGHWAY)\n\nwww.git-india.edu.in\n* Sriman Chandulal Sheth High School & Jr.College.\n* Navabharat High School & Junior College, Bharne.\n* L. P. English School.\n* L. T. T. English Medium School & Junior College.\n* M. I. Hajwani English Medium School & Junior College.\n* Rotary English Medium School.\n* Shiv Shankar Madhyamik Vidyalaya & Jr. College, Kulwandi.\n{{clear}}\n* Haji SM Mukaddam Highschool and Junior College.\n* Dnyandeep Vidya Mandir, Bhadgaon.\n* Vishwakarma Sahajeevan Institute of Management.\n* New English Junior College of Aambavali\n* Yogita Dental College Khed.\n* S.I.Junior college, furus, khed\n* New English school, Dayal, Khed\n* I.C.S College Khed\n* Ideal English school Furus\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Saitavde]]\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"4\" | '''Khed (KHED)'''\n|-\n|style=\"width:30%;\" rowspan=\"2\" |Next 'Small' station towards Mumbai:<br />'''Diwankhauti'''\n|style=\"width:40%;\" colspan=\"2\" |'''Konkan Railway : Railway (India)\n|style=\"width:30%;\" rowspan=\"2\" |Next 'Small' station from Mumbai:<br />'''Anjani'''\n|\n|-\n|'''Distance from Mumbai (CST) = 0275&nbsp;km'''\n|-\n|style=\"width:30%;\" rowspan=\"2\" |Next 'Main' station towards Mumbai:<br />'''[[Mangaon]]'''\n|style=\"width:40%;\" colspan=\"2\" |'''Konkan Railway : Railway (India)\n|style=\"width:30%;\" rowspan=\"2\" |Next 'Main' station from Mumbai:<br />'''[[Chiplun]]'''\n|}\n\n*\n*\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Ratnagiri district topics}}\n\n[[Category:Talukas in Maharashtra]]\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Ratnagiri district]]\n\n[[pt:Rajgurunagar (Khed)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2017}}\n{{more citations needed|date=August 2014}}\n\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name = Khed\n| other_name   = \n| nickname                = \n| settlement_type         = town\n| image_skyline           = Khed Naringi River.jpg\n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = Naringi River, which flows through Khed\n| pushpin_map             = India#India Maharashtra\n| pushpin_label_position  = right\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Maharashtra, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|17|43|04|N|73|23|38|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Maharashtra]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of district